  - Varying column counts per row (the table will use the maximum number of columns from any row and pad shorter rows with empty cells).
- Styling for the table, including:
  - Alternating row colors (zebra striping).
  - Clear borders for better readability.

This is a single file, so you can save it as `csv-to-table.html` and open it in any modern web browser. It uses vanilla JavaScript for parsing and doesn't rely on any external libraries.

